quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  3,46,"And he will speak to people in the cradle and in adulthood and will be one of the righteous.”"
  3,47,"She said, “My Lord, how can I have a child when no human being has touched me?” He said, “So shall it be! Allah creates whatever He wills. Whenever He decrees a matter, He only says to it, <span class=""h"">‘Be,’ and so it is<sup foot_note=""79770"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>."
  3,48,"And <span class=""h"">He<sup foot_note=""79771"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">will teach him</span>scribing{2}and wisdom and the Torah and the Gospel.",footnotes:2:The Arabic word used is al-kitabwhich may mean ‘scribing’ or ‘scripture’.
  3,49,"And<i class=""s"">(He will appoint him as) </i>a messenger to the Children of Israel<i class=""s"">(to proclaim) </i>: ‘I have come to you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>with a sign from your <span class=""h"">Lord: that I<sup foot_note=""79773"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">create</span>for you out of clay the shape of a bird, then I breathe into it so it becomes a bird by Allah’s leave; and I heal the born-blind and the leper; and I revive the dead by Allah’s leave; and I inform you concerning what you eat and what you store in your houses. Indeed, in that is a sign for you, if you are believers."
  3,50,"And I am to confirm what preceded me of the Torah and to make lawful to you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>some of what was prohibited for you. And I have come to you with a sign from your Lord, so be mindful of Allah and obey me."
  3,51,"Indeed, Allah is my Lord and your Lord, so worship Him. That is a straight path.’”"
  3,52,"So when Jesus sensed denial on their part, he said, “Who are my supporters towards Allah?” The disciples said, “We are Allah’s supporters; we have attained faith in Allah, so bear witness that we are indeed Muslims{1}.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Muslimoonwhich means those who willingly submit to God, regardless of which prophet they followed.
